      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "This PHP version is at the time of writing more than 6 years old, and a quick search in the Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVE) database showed that this framework suffers from 69 known security vulnerabilities, six of which received the most severe impact score of 10. Consequently, the vulnerabilities range from simple DoS attacks, access control bypassing, and cross-site scripting to arbitrary code execution on the server."
